-line\" y1=\"153.109375\" y2=\"0\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"1.5px\" marker-end=\"url(#arrow)\"></line><text class=\"y-axis-label\" style=\"text-anchor: middle; dominant-baseline: text-after-edge; font-family: Noto Serif; font-style: italic; fill: currentColor; font-size: 15px;\" transform=\"translate(0,-12)\">y</text></g><text x=\"0\" y=\"138.109375\" dx=\"-13.25px\" dy=\"13.5px\" fill=\"currentColor\" style=\"font-size: 15px; font-style: italic; font-family: Noto Serif;\">O</text><path d=\"M0,45.461L119.119,138.109\" stroke=\"black\" stroke-width=\"2px\" fill=\"none\" stroke-dasharray=\"none\"></path></g><g class=\"xtitle-group\" transform=\"translate(267.2734375, 194.109375)\"><text class=\"xtitle-group-line-0\" transform=\"translate(0, 0)\" fill=\"currentColor\" style=\"font-family: Noto Serif; font-size: 15px; text-anchor: middle; dominant-baseline: hanging;\">Number of T-shirts</text></g><g class=\"ytitle-group\" transform=\"translate(81.609375, 94.0546875)\"><text class=\"ytitle-group-line-0\" transform=\"translate(0, 0)\" fill=\"currentColor\" style=\"font-family: Noto Serif; font-size: 15px; text-anchor: middle; dominant-baseline: text-before-edge;\">Number of sweatshirts</text></g></svg><div role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Long description for graph of a line\" class=\"sr-only\"><ul>\n<li>The line slants gradually down from left to right.</li>\n<li>The line passes through the following points:<br/>\n<ul>\n<li>(0 comma 35)</li>\n<li>(90 comma 0)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div></figure></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The graph models the relationship between the number of T-shirts, <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math>, and the number of sweatshirts, <math alttext=\"y\"><mi>y</mi>\n</math>, that Kira can purchase for a school fundraiser. Which equation could represent this relationship?</p>",
